// Man page for web
manWeb="WEB(1)                           X Shell Manual                           WEB(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    web - Private HTTP interweb service
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>web</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    The web command installs and launches a private HTTP server for secure
    browsing of coin, bank, repository, and internet rental services. The
    server is not port forwarded and operates as a local service only.
    Requires root privileges to execute. The service automatically closes
    when the terminal is closed. Repository access is limited to fetching
    files only, without account creation or file download capabilities.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>web</b> - Launch Interweb Service
      Initiates the private HTTP interweb service.
      Provides safe browsing for financial and repository services.
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Launch Service</color>
    <b>web</b>
    Start the private HTTP server

    <color=#e4ff34># Access Services</color>
    <b>web</b>
    Browse coin services securely

    <b>web</b>
    Access bank services privately

    <b>web</b>
    View repository files safely

    <color=#e4ff34># Service Features</color>
    <b>web</b>
    No port forwarding (local only)

    <b>web</b>
    Auto-closes on terminal exit

    <b>web</b>
    Repository fetch capability

    <color=#e4ff34># Security Notes</color>
    <b>web</b>
    Requires root privileges

    <b>web</b>
    Cannot create accounts or download files

    <b>web</b>
    Limited repo functionality
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>service</b>, <b>open</b>, <b>start</b>"